<h1>Communities</h1>

<p>NOTF works with neighbourhoods across India. Here are the active communities in our network.</p>

<section>
    <h2>Bengaluru</h2>

    <article class="community-card">
        <h3>Vasanthnagar</h3>
        <p><strong>Lead Organization:</strong> Center for Civic Participation (C4C)</p>
        <p><strong>Focus Areas:</strong> Urban heat mitigation, Rooftop gardens, Greening, Community engagement</p>
        <p><strong>Population:</strong> ~15,000 residents</p>

        <h4>About</h4>
        <p>Vasanthnagar is a centrally located neighbourhood in Bengaluru with a mix of
        residential buildings and commercial establishments. The community has been
        experiencing increasing urban heat due to reduced green cover.</p>

        <h4>Current Initiatives</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Rooftop Gardens Program - 15+ gardens installed</li>
            <li>Native plant species focus</li>
            <li>Water conservation initiatives</li>
            <li>Urban cooling through greening</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>Achievements</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>15 rooftop gardens installed</li>
            <li>50+ residents trained</li>
            <li>Measurable temperature reduction (3-5 degrees C)</li>
            <li>Strong community participation</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Status:</strong> Active since June 2024</p>
    </article>
</section>

